        <link rel="schema.DC" href="https://purl.org/DC/elements/1.0/" /><meta name="citation_journal_title" content="RadioGraphics" /><meta name="dc.Title" content="Liver Iron Quantification with MR Imaging: A Primer for Radiologists" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Roxanne  Labranche" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Guillaume  Gilbert" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Milena  Cerny" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Kim-Nhien  Vu" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Denis  Soulières" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Damien  Olivié" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Jean-Sébastien  Billiard" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Takeshi  Yokoo" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="An  Tang" /><meta name="dc.Description" content="This review describes MR imaging techniques for liver iron quantification and provides an overview of common causes, complications, and treatments of liver iron overload, with discussion of pitfall..." /><meta name="Description" content="This review describes MR imaging techniques for liver iron quantification and provides an overview of common causes, complications, and treatments of liver iron overload, with discussion of pitfall..." /><meta name="dc.Description" content="Iron overload is a systemic disorder and is either primary (genetic) or secondary (exogenous iron administration). Primary iron overload is most commonly associated with hereditary hemochromatosis ..." /><meta name="Description" content="Iron overload is a systemic disorder and is either primary (genetic) or secondary (exogenous iron administration). Primary iron overload is most commonly associated with hereditary hemochromatosis ..." /><meta name="dc.Publisher" content="Radiological Society of North America" /><meta name="dc.Date" scheme="WTN8601" content="2018-03-12" /><meta name="dc.Type" content="research-article" /><meta name="dc.Format" content="text/HTML" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="manuscript" content="170079" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="